Fresh Pi session: CREATE A PR DRAFT (agentic).

Inputs:
- PR number (the PR whose comments we addressed): {{inputs.pr-number}}
- Review report (latest round): {{run.dir}}/review/report-{{run.round}}.md
- Manual-testing report (latest round): {{run.dir}}/manual-testing/report-{{run.round}}.md
- Execution summary (latest round): {{run.dir}}/execution/summary-{{run.round}}.md
- Worktree (repository root): {{run.worktree-dir}}

Goal:
Draft the title and body for a NEW pull request on the fix branch (the implementation branch recorded in design/branch-name.txt). This PR addresses the comments on the original PR #{{inputs.pr-number}}.

Rules:
- Inspect the worktree diff to summarize what changed and why.
- Title: concise imperative summary (no trailing newline beyond one).
- Body: markdown — reference the original PR number, summarize the addressed comments, list the change items, and note how they were validated (tests + manual testing + review).
- Do not push or create the PR here; that is the deterministic push-pr step.
- Do not edit source code.

Write:
- Title: {{run.dir}}/pr/pr-title.txt
- Body: {{run.dir}}/pr/pr-body.md
- Status JSON: {{run.dir}}/pr/draft-status.json

Status JSON examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"drafted title + body","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"could not summarize diff","issues_file":null}